comment: Stuckey (IND) obtains a legal guarding position as he defends Wade's (MIA) driving shot attempt. Any contact on the play is initiated by Wade.
Winslow (MIA) makes contact with George's (IND) arm that affects his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Mahinmi (IND) sets the screen on Dragic (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Mahinmi (IND) legally contests Bosh's (MIA) fadeaway jump shot attempt.

Dragic (MIA) commits a take foul on Stuckey (IND). The officials determined that when the illegal contact was first made, the defender had his head and shoulders ahead of the offensive player, eliminating the chance of a clear path foul.
Bosh (MIA) extends his hip as he sets the screen on George (IND) without giving him room to avoid the contact.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Wade (MIA) released the shot prior to the clock expiring was confirmed.
RHH shows that Mahinmi (IND) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Bosh's (MIA) post shot attempt.
Allen (IND) sets the screen on Dragic (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Allen (IND) dislodges Wade (MIA), affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Dragic (MIA) sets the screen on Stuckey (IND) and gives him room to avoid the contact.

Mahinmi (IND) makes contact with Bosh's (MIA) body that affects his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Correctly called 24 second violation.
